        <bold>Search starting points can be gene, disease or drug. Why can’t users search by other starting points e.g. tissue?</bold>
      </p>
      <p>Technically, this should be possible. however, with the three provided starting points, all other searches are technically possible using basic Cytoscape functions. </p>
      <p>
        <bold>The last update date of the ICT database and the date and version used for each resource should be clearly communicated to the user e.g. via the manuscript, app and/or ICT website.</bold>
